                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18219</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from"
                            >Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-22T23:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1916, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Am convinced that basis for Government anxiety and alarm is matter reported
                    by Silliman from Saltillo in his May 19, 4 p.m., relating to statement Governor
                    Coahuila concerning probable attack on American troops in that State. Understand
                    Cabinet here repudiates alleged orders mentioned by Governor and is doing all
                    possible to stop Mexican forces. They fear can not reach them in time to avoid
                    trouble.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
